# .trivyignore

# --- cert-manager (Jetstack upstream manifest, k8s/cert-manager/cert-manager.yaml) ---
# These are cert-manager's required-by-design permissions, not misconfigurations.
# Do not remove these permissions in the manifest itself — cert-manager will break.

# cert-manager needs cluster-scoped Secret access: it stores every issued TLS cert as a Secret
AVD-KSV-0041

# cainjector needs to modify webhook configs to inject CA bundles (core CA injection function)
AVD-KSV-0114

# ACME HTTP-01 challenge solver needs to manage Services/Ingresses to serve challenge responses
AVD-KSV-0056

# cert-manager images are pulled from quay.io (Jetstack's registry) — legitimate, just not
# in Trivy's default trusted-registry allowlist
AVD-KSV-0125

# --- Terraform (modules/vpc/main.tf) ---
# Public IP accepted: ingress restricted to SSH from allowed_ssh_cidr only,
# no NAT gateway budget for this project. Re-evaluate if instance count/exposure grows.
AVD-AWS-0164

# --- Terraform (modules/ec2/main.tf) ---
# These findings are accepted for the current self-managed learning cluster design.

# EC2 nodes require outbound HTTPS access for:
# - pulling container images from registries
# - OS package updates
# - Let's Encrypt ACME validation
# - Kubernetes component communication with external services
# Restrict further if NAT gateways, VPC endpoints, or egress proxies are introduced.
AVD-AWS-0104

# Root EBS encryption omitted intentionally for the existing learning cluster.
# Enabling encryption would require EC2 instance replacement and migration of
# local-path-provisioner volumes and PostgreSQL data.
# Enable for future cluster rebuilds or production environments.
AVD-AWS-0131

# --- local-path-provisioner (Rancher upstream manifest, k8s/storage/local-path-provisioner.yaml) ---
# These findings are accepted because local-path-provisioner requires host filesystem access
# to create and manage PersistentVolume directories on cluster nodes.

# local-path-provisioner writes directories on the host filesystem for PV provisioning,
# so an immutable root filesystem is not practical.
AVD-KSV-0014

# local-path-provisioner runs with upstream defaults and requires elevated filesystem access
# to manage host-backed storage paths.
AVD-KSV-0118